ication. That might simplify the process and ensure everything aligns correctly when checking for resource bundles. I need to think about how this approach helps avoid potential conflicts or confusion with multiple keys. Simplifying this could lead to a smoother process overall. It's definitely worth exploring further for clarity!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_I4FEi65ZW6nB9cJa6qShCEi7|fc_0158544c1cfabf85016a406042674c819487b4242dc63be2c2", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework/spring-beans/5.3.15/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_beans/ResourceBundleEditorTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_springframework.spring_beans;\n\nimport java.util.ResourceBundle;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.springframework.beans.propertyeditors.ResourceBundleEditor;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class ResourceBundleEditorTest {\n\n    private static final String BASE_NAME = \"springbeans.messages.ResourceBundleEditorMessages\";\n\n    private final ResourceBundleEditor editor = new ResourceBundleEditor();\n\n    @Test\n    void loadsResourceBundleFromBaseName() {\n        editor.setAsText(BASE_NAME);\n\n        ResourceBundle bundle = (ResourceBundle) editor.getValue();\n\n        assertThat(bundle.getString(\"baseOnly\")).isEqualTo(\"base bundle\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void loadsResourceBundleFromBaseNameAndLocale() {\n        editor.setAsText(BASE_NAME + \"_en_GB\");\n\n        ResourceBundle bundle = (ResourceBundle) editor.getValue();\n\n        assertThat(bundle.getString(\"message\")).isEqualTo(\"localized British English bundle\");\n        assertThat(bundle.getString(\"localeOnly\")).isEqualTo(\"locale-specific value\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void fallsBackToBaseNameWhenLocaleSuffixIsEmpty() {\n        editor.setAsText(BASE_NAME + \"_\");\n\n        ResourceBundle bundle = (ResourceBundle) editor.getValue();\n\n        assertThat(bundle.getString(\"baseOnly\")).isEqualTo(\"base bundle\");\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 957, "output": 1128, "cacheRead": 16384, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 18469, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782603831882, "responseId": "resp_0158544c1cfabf85016a40603844588194abe2377a135478c9"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_I4FEi65ZW6nB9cJa6qShCEi7|fc_0158544c1cfabf85016a406042674c819487b4242dc63be2c2", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1539 bytes to tests/src/org.springframework/spring-beans/5.3.15/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_beans/ResourceBundleEditorTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1782603845192}]}
